Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.49,0:00:08.90,main,STUDENT,0000,0000,0000,,E-Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.17,0:00:10.86,Club_application_00:09(Ep 17),SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Club Application
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.21,0:00:13.81,main,STUDENT,0000,0000,0000,,We saw your article \Nin the paper and your website!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.81,0:00:16.01,main,STUDENT,0000,0000,0000,,You guys are the best! Please let us join you!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.01,0:00:18.83,main,NICO,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, uh... You want to join the team?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.25,0:00:21.28,main,NICO,0000,0000,0000,,Wait. Why are you asking me?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.28,0:00:23.31,main,STUDENT,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you the coach?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.12,0:00:24.98,main,NICO,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.55,0:00:39.97,Series_Title,NICO,0000,0000,0000,,Run with the Wind
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.40,0:02:02.89,main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,You can clear away all the ash you want,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.89,0:02:06.26,main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,but the road to anti-aging is long. Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.26,0:02:07.94,main,NICO,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.16,0:02:10.51,main,MUSA,0000,0000,0000,,I appreciate their enthusiasm, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.04,0:02:12.40,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,I put up a note.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.40,0:02:15.36,Apologies_02:12(Ep 17),SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,To individuals wishing to join the Kansei University Long Distance Track and Field Team\NThe Kansei University Long Distance Track and Field Team is not currently recruiting new members.\NPlease accept our apologies.\NWe appreciate your understanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.71,0:02:15.08,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,We'll continue rejecting applicants.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.36,0:02:17.30,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Aotake is full right now,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.30,0:02:20.07,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,and I don't want to be influenced\Nby any passing fads.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.80,0:02:23.55,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have time to look after new members,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.55,0:02:25.08,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,and I want to focus on the ten of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.70,0:02:28.96,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,If anyone approaches you at school, \Npolitely turn them down.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.96,0:02:30.61,main,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.32,0:02:34.13,main,SHINDO,0000,0000,0000,,We're drowning in interview requests, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.13,0:02:36.88,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Choose carefully from the offers\Nand reject as many as you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.88,0:02:39.94,main,KING,0000,0000,0000,,What? But we could be famous.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.94,0:02:42.14,main,NICO,0000,0000,0000,,Shouldn't you be looking for a job?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.51,0:02:45.15,main,MUSA,0000,0000,0000,,I can only assume he's\Ntrying not to think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.15,0:02:46.74,main,SHINDO,0000,0000,0000,,What about Nippon TV?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.74,0:02:49.31,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,We'll continue doing whatever\Nwe started before the qualifier.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.31,0:02:51.35,main,SHINDO,0000,0000,0000,,Got it. Oh, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.35,0:02:55.36,main,SHINDO,0000,0000,0000,,Can we discuss water station\Nstaff and volunteers later?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.36,0:02:56.32,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.74,0:03:00.81,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm also thinking about checking\Nout the course next weekend.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.44,0:03:05.18,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,We can't run it, but it's\Nworth just looking at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.18,0:03:06.49,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Keep your schedules open.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.49,0:03:08.09,main,KING,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go to the hot springs on the way back.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.09,0:03:08.85,main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.85,0:03:10.08,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,Question.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.34,0:03:13.40,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,We can't. We have plans that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.40,0:03:16.72,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,We're playing soccer with \Nsome friends from language class.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.72,0:03:17.75,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Cancel your plans.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.09,0:03:20.17,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,What? But they won't have enough players.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.17,0:03:21.73,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,We'd be inconveniencing them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.73,0:03:24.30,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,There's still time. Find some substitutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.77,0:03:28.00,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Not even professionals\Ncan afford to run unprepared.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.00,0:03:31.25,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, soccer? What if you got injured?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.95,0:03:34.24,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Hakone comes first. Don't forget that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.24,0:03:35.15,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, listen.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.48,0:03:37.81,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,Is there any point in obsessing over it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.30,0:03:46.41,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,You've been tricking us, haven't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.77,0:03:51.49,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,When you recruited us,\Nyou said we'd aim for the top!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.49,0:03:52.69,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,That's impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.69,0:03:54.38,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,Just look at our time! It's clear as day!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.38,0:03:57.84,Final_results_03:54(Ep 17),SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Shinsei University 10:15:21\NKanagawa International University 10:16:03\NKansei University 10:16:43\NOka University 10:17:44\NYakuo University 10:19:52
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.82,0:03:58.49,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how hard we try, we're not\Nstrong enough to beat the seeded teams!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.49,0:04:00.03,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,It's impossible for us to win!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.16,0:04:04.93,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,You knew that and wheedled us\Nanyway, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.85,0:04:10.18,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,You're right that I said we'd aim for the top.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.18,0:04:10.89,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,But—
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.89,0:04:13.47,main,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,See? See?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.47,0:04:14.92,main,MUSA,0000,0000,0000,,Wait. Calm down.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.33,0:04:19.81,main,MUSA,0000,0000,0000,,Is it really impossible for us to win \Nno matter how hard we try?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.81,0:04:21.11,main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,It's impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.11,0:04:24.28,main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,The twins are right. Our time proves it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.28,0:04:29.24,main,NICO,0000,0000,0000,,Especially in long distance,\Nit's rare to see an upset.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.24,0:04:33.39,main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Even Rikudo's second team\Nis way better than us.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.39,0:04:36.21,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,You guys knew.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.21,0:04:38.19,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,That's not fair!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.16,0:04:43.59,main,PRINCE,0000,0000,0000,,But, depending on how \Nyou look at it, we're lucky.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.86,0:04:49.56,main,PRINCE,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how fast you are, only a\Nhandful of runners get to run at Hakone.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.20,0:04:54.02,main,PRINCE,0000,0000,0000,,But we made it through the qualifier.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.02,0:04:56.62,main,PRINCE,0000,0000,0000,,We get to run at Hakone, just like we wanted.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.46,0:05:01.98,main,PRINCE,0000,0000,0000,,There are plenty of people\Nwho'd be jealous of that alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.98,0:05:04.70,main,KING,0000,0000,0000,,You're not wrong, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.70,0:05:06.85,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,There's no point if we can't win!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.85,0:05:10.91,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! There's no point in competing\Nwhen you already know the outcome!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.21,0:05:14.62,main,KAKERU,0000,0000,0000,,Then you shouldn't be playing soccer.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.92,0:05:17.29,main,KAKERU,0000,0000,0000,,If you want to win, you should be training.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.70,0:05:19.30,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,You think you're so great.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.30,0:05:21.92,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,We're saying we can't find\Nthe motivation to do that!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.92,0:05:26.01,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! How can you say that after\Nyou couldn't respond the other day?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.96,0:05:29.46,main,NICO,0000,0000,0000,,Enough, guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.91,0:05:33.97,main,KAKERU,0000,0000,0000,,If you guys can't run because you can't win,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.97,0:05:37.22,main,KAKERU,0000,0000,0000,,will you quit living \Nbecause you'll die someday?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.22,0:05:39.44,main,KAKERU,0000,0000,0000,,Is that how it is? It is, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.44,0:05:41.69,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,What are you trying to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.69,0:05:43.52,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,Here he goes again.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.52,0:05:45.66,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,Kakeru's making ridiculous arguments again.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.40,0:05:49.78,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,I'll never die. Never.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.78,0:05:52.74,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,Quibble, quibble. Here comes the quibbler.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.74,0:05:55.06,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,To be or not to be? That's the question.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.06,0:05:56.50,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,But I'll never die.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.50,0:05:59.75,main,KAKERU,0000,0000,0000,,Listen to me! What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.75,0:06:03.17,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,Kakeru the quibbler will never die.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.31,0:06:02.21,main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,What are we doing right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.22,0:06:10.14,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you had a question for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.34,0:06:17.52,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,You're right that I mentioned the top, \Nbut I didn't mean we'd win.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.52,0:06:20.48,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,What did you mean, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.24,0:06:23.39,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm searching for that answer, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.27,0:06:27.01,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm searching for the destination.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.68,0:06:29.17,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,What it means to run.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.25,0:06:32.57,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,This is stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.08,0:06:34.58,main,MUSA,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.07,0:06:37.40,main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Kakeru, it's your turn to do the dishes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.40,0:06:38.41,main,KAKERU,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.41,0:06:41.63,main,NICO,0000,0000,0000,,Just because. Learn to keep your cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.67,0:06:48.59,main,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,Searching for the Answer
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.34,0:06:58.27,main,SHINDO,0000,0000,0000,,Haiji.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.27,0:07:00.23,Chikusei_so_06:58(Ep 17),SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Chikusei-so
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.19,0:07:00.23,main,SHINDO,0000,0000,0000,,The twins aren't here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.15,0:07:03.33,main,KING,0000,0000,0000,,They actually blew us off.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.33,0:07:04.69,main,KAKERU,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.65,0:07:08.09,main,KAKERU,0000,0000,0000,,It's because I couldn't answer them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.09,0:07:12.55,main,KAKERU,0000,0000,0000,,On the way home from the qualifier,\Nthey asked me why we're running.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.62,0:07:19.34,main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but it's like not being able to tell\Nsomeone what the meaning of life is.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.94,0:07:22.08,main,NICO,0000,0000,0000,,Nice quibble.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.01,0:07:27.42,main,KAKERU,0000,0000,0000,,We made it through the qualifier.\NWe're running at Hakone together.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.42,0:07:31.34,main,KAKERU,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe we've already achieved\Nthe first goal we set for ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.34,0:07:34.68,main,KAKERU,0000,0000,0000,,But that wasn't the real top.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.76,0:07:37.61,main,KAKERU,0000,0000,0000,,I knew that, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.61,0:07:40.83,main,KAKERU,0000,0000,0000,,After all, I wanted to aim even\Nhigher with you guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.59,0:07:43.73,main,KAKERU,0000,0000,0000,,But I hesitated to answer them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.76,0:07:45.77,main,MUSA,0000,0000,0000,,Kakeru...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.52,0:08:04.30,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,We haven't played soccer in forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.30,0:08:05.15,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.57,0:08:08.09,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,We've just been running this whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.82,0:08:09.80,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.24,0:08:13.42,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,Do you regret it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.64,0:08:16.05,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,Choosing this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.55,0:08:18.51,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,Nah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.51,0:08:21.40,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,We made these plans first.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.40,0:08:24.70,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,You're right. We're running at Hakone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.70,0:08:28.07,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,Now we just have to practice\Nenough that they won't complain.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.07,0:08:29.28,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,Complain?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.28,0:08:29.98,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.26,0:08:34.20,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,So who won't complain? Haiji?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.61,0:08:38.49,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,The guys who didn't qualify?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.49,0:08:39.53,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.77,0:08:43.93,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,I hope everyone shows up soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.93,0:08:46.25,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,We got in the habit of waking up early.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.25,0:08:48.63,main,KAKERU,0000,0000,0000,,Joji! Jota!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.69,0:08:52.01,main,KAKERU,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.49,0:08:53.97,main,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,Who is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.41,0:08:56.43,main,KAKERU,0000,0000,0000,,Hakone!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.86,0:08:59.97,main,KAKERU,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone's waiting!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.64,0:09:01.91,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,What's he doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.91,0:09:03.43,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,Who crashes a soccer game?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.78,0:09:07.25,main,KAKERU,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go to Hakone!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.25,0:09:09.11,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,Crap! Let's run!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.11,0:09:10.96,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,But he's one of the best in the country!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.96,0:09:13.01,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,He's running at us while smiling!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.01,0:09:14.67,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,Stay away!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.65,0:09:15.79,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,It's no use! He's catching up!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.92,0:09:17.27,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,Jota! Don't give up!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.21,0:09:34.89,main,NICO,0000,0000,0000,,Nicely done.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.89,0:09:37.93,main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way you were outrunning him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.48,0:09:40.68,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,I can't run anymore...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.31,0:09:44.43,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,I don't consent to this...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.43,0:09:48.31,Hakone's_sections(Ep 17),SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Section 1 Starting Line Yomiuri Shimbun Tokyo Office
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.71,0:09:52.73,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,This is the starting line.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.73,0:09:55.53,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,The day of the race, the crowds \Non the sidewalk will be a hundred deep.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.79,0:09:58.99,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,They'll build a huge stage out front,\Nand cameras will be pointed at the runners.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.99,0:10:00.66,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,It's a truly grand occasion.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.66,0:10:03.37,main,NICO,0000,0000,0000,,Will we have time to think about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.37,0:10:05.62,main,PRINCE,0000,0000,0000,,It's not for the sensitive.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.62,0:10:07.41,main,MUSA,0000,0000,0000,,The wind between the buildings is fierce.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.41,0:10:09.25,main,SHINDO,0000,0000,0000,,Our bodies will get cold quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.25,0:10:12.92,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Twenty-one runners will \Nbegin running amidst the crowd,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.92,0:10:17.26,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,thinking only of delivering their sash\Nto their teammate waiting far ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.36,0:10:26.67,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Let's keep moving.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.31,0:10:29.77,Hakone's_sections(Ep 17),SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Section 2 (Section 10) Tsurumi Relay Station
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.61,0:10:35.37,main,KING,0000,0000,0000,,Don't they stop all the traffic here\Nand turn this into part of the course?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.37,0:10:36.61,main,KING,0000,0000,0000,,That's amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.61,0:10:39.46,main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,It's way too much pageantry\Nfor a bunch of college students.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.46,0:10:41.83,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,It means it's worth just that much.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.83,0:10:44.79,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Our running should be worthy of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.79,0:10:45.63,main,SHINDO,0000,0000,0000,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.70,0:10:51.35,main,PRINCE,0000,0000,0000,,Have you gotten better at driving?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.35,0:10:52.79,main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.79,0:10:56.20,main,KING,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't believe it, but you have, haven't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.20,0:10:59.53,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,It's not fair for me to only\Nexpect you guys to grow.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.53,0:11:00.76,main,NICO,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, cut that out.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.76,0:11:05.10,main,NICO,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't keep sucking at driving, \Nwe won't be able to make excuses anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.36,0:11:08.77,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, last year in this section 2,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.77,0:11:14.37,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Kofu's Iwanki and Rikudo's\NFujioka put on a legendary sprint.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.12,0:11:16.74,main,KING,0000,0000,0000,,The Glorious Section 2, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.74,0:11:18.89,main,MUSA,0000,0000,0000,,They call it the ace's section.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.89,0:11:19.79,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Kakeru.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.09,0:11:22.24,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Do you want to run it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.65,0:11:27.74,main,KAKERU,0000,0000,0000,,No matter the section,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.41,0:11:31.25,main,KAKERU,0000,0000,0000,,as long as there's a road,\NI'll run as hard as I can.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.47,0:11:35.39,main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Did you hear that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.39,0:11:37.50,main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,He said as long as there's a road.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.62,0:11:42.56,main,KAKERU,0000,0000,0000,,Was what I said really that weird? Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.89,0:11:46.33,main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no. Your words were encouraging.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.35,0:11:49.27,Hakone's_sections(Ep 17),SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Section 3 (Section 9) Totsuka Relay Station
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.98,0:11:52.94,Shonan_Bridge_11:51(Ep 17),SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Shonan Bridge
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.45,0:11:56.40,main,KING,0000,0000,0000,,Yeesh.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.40,0:11:58.01,main,KING,0000,0000,0000,,The sea breeze is strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.78,0:12:02.26,main,MUSA,0000,0000,0000,,It feels nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.26,0:12:03.28,main,SHINDO,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.28,0:12:04.49,Hakone's_sections(Ep 17),SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Section 4 (Section 8) Hiratsuka Relay Station
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.95,0:12:07.41,Hakone's_sections(Ep 17),SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Section 5 (Section 7) Odawara Relay Station
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.75,0:12:10.82,main,KING,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.82,0:12:12.79,main,KING,0000,0000,0000,,We're finally here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.84,0:12:25.97,main,NICO,0000,0000,0000,,It's steeper than I imagined.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.27,0:12:28.89,main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Going up this will be hell,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.89,0:12:31.78,main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,but this means the downhill\Nis no joke, either, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.78,0:12:32.72,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.72,0:12:34.43,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Naturally, the strength of your\Nlegs are important in this section,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.43,0:12:36.90,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,but your courage and\Nintelligence matter, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.36,0:12:40.07,Nat'l_Route_12:38(Ep 17),SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,National Route 1 Summit Level
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.96,0:12:40.07,main,KING,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.07,0:12:41.71,main,KING,0000,0000,0000,,This is the highest point?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.48,0:12:45.10,main,KING,0000,0000,0000,,So the finish line isn't at the top.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.97,0:12:49.66,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,We're almost at the finish\Nline of the first half.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.10,0:12:52.54,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Let's enjoy the scenery while we can.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.58,0:12:58.04,Hakone's_sections(Ep 17),SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,First Half Finish Line (Section 6 Starting Line) Lake Ashi
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.82,0:13:04.22,main,MUSA,0000,0000,0000,,Beautiful...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.43,0:13:09.04,main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,This is awesome.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.04,0:13:12.09,main,NICO,0000,0000,0000,,The air at Aotake doesn't compare to this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.09,0:13:15.32,main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,That was mostly your fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.37,0:13:19.20,main,SHINDO,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder what it'll be like\Nthe day of the race.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.20,0:13:21.57,main,KING,0000,0000,0000,,There will be screaming crowds, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.98,0:13:24.03,main,PRINCE,0000,0000,0000,,Guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.41,0:13:28.65,main,PRINCE,0000,0000,0000,,In the parking lot...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.53,0:13:33.95,main,KOSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,You're so eager. You're\Neven previewing the course.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.74,0:13:38.08,main,KOSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry I called you plebs once.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.76,0:13:41.55,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Should you be loafing around here?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.55,0:13:43.80,main,KOSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,I'm waiting for Group B to arrive.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.18,0:13:45.94,main,KOSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,I'm in Group A.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.94,0:13:47.43,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,He's a regular?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.43,0:13:48.26,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.60,0:13:50.49,main,KOSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah. That qualifier.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.49,0:13:53.67,main,KOSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,It's amazing that you were\Nneck and neck with Iwanki.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.67,0:13:56.23,main,KOSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,I bet you could run the real thing right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.61,0:13:57.94,main,KAKERU,0000,0000,0000,,That's not true.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.90,0:14:00.11,main,KOSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,So modest.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.74,0:14:02.57,main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,What are you guys doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.28,0:14:04.78,main,KOSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,You're all here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.29,0:14:07.45,main,KOSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,We were just talking...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.06,0:14:11.87,main,KOSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,...about what I'd do if I were a Kansei runner.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.06,0:14:17.21,main,KOSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, no matter how much you\Npractice, you only have ten runners.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.21,0:14:20.08,main,KOSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,If even one of you caught a cold...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.86,0:14:29.44,main,KOSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,And even if you run like crazy\Nand finish in the top ten,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.44,0:14:32.14,main,KOSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,your oldest runners will graduate.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.96,0:14:38.00,main,KOSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,There's no point in earning a seed for \Nnext year if you don't have enough runners.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.57,0:14:43.70,main,KOSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you wonder what you're running for?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.64,0:14:48.92,main,KOSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,It must be hard to stay motivated.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.92,0:14:50.61,main,STUDENT,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Sakaki!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.02,0:14:52.79,main,STUDENT,0000,0000,0000,,Group B is here!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.79,0:14:53.58,main,KOSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,Got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.30,0:14:58.25,main,KOSUKE,0000,0000,0000,,See you somewhere on the course.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.45,0:15:02.46,main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,You sure you guys aren't\Nconnected by a red string of fate?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.99,0:15:04.92,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,In some ways, he's diligent.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.75,0:15:06.65,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Don't mind him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.65,0:15:09.57,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Consider it progress that no one responded.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.02,0:15:13.68,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,I can't!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.32,0:15:16.64,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,I am bothered!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.64,0:15:18.87,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn't you talk back to him?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.87,0:15:22.32,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,Tell us why you run!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.32,0:15:25.82,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,I told you, I'm searching \Nfor that answer right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.75,0:15:34.37,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go somewhere else.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.40,0:15:41.95,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Sakaki was probably trying to say
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.33,0:15:46.57,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,that improving yourself by competing\Nagainst strong runners from strong schools
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.57,0:15:49.53,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,is how an athlete should be\Nand is a reason to run.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.18,0:15:53.03,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,But is he right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.03,0:15:56.73,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Can you say what we're doing is wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.52,0:16:03.52,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,It's true that we need every one of us. \NThere's no arguing that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.52,0:16:06.47,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know what will happen\Nnext year or the year after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.96,0:16:09.83,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure those who empathize\Nwith us will follow.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.83,0:16:14.00,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,All I can do is believe in that \Nand run as hard as I can right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.11,0:16:18.68,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,So there's no need to respond to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.68,0:16:22.46,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,All we can do is acknowledge his points\Nand move forward despite them.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.43,0:16:26.38,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Does that answer your question?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.08,0:16:31.97,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.97,0:16:32.97,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.38,0:16:36.09,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,We like what you have to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.06,0:16:40.68,main,NICO,0000,0000,0000,,Like, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.09,0:16:43.30,main,PRINCE,0000,0000,0000,,That feels like enough to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.30,0:16:45.17,main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be swayed by your emotions.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.17,0:16:46.65,main,YUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Debate until you're satisfied.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.65,0:16:49.61,main,KING,0000,0000,0000,,The twins aren't theorists like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.25,0:17:12.09,main,HANAKO,0000,0000,0000,,You had a fight?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.09,0:17:14.18,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't call it a fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.18,0:17:16.48,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,I understand what he's trying to say, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.48,0:17:21.26,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,I want to accept what he's saying,\Nbut it feels like he tricked us.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.64,0:17:24.79,main,HANAKO,0000,0000,0000,,I know what you mean. Haiji is so calm.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.79,0:17:29.94,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. We missed our opportunity\Nto return to normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.94,0:17:33.23,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,It's not like we were wrong, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.88,0:17:38.70,main,HANAKO,0000,0000,0000,,I think you should believe him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.15,0:17:44.81,main,HANAKO,0000,0000,0000,,He's been patiently thinking for four years.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.81,0:17:48.16,main,HANAKO,0000,0000,0000,,I can believe him because he's come this far.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.22,0:17:51.84,main,HANAKO,0000,0000,0000,,Compared to all the time\NHaiji has spent on it,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.84,0:17:55.51,main,HANAKO,0000,0000,0000,,our next two months will fly by in a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.19,0:18:00.33,main,HANAKO,0000,0000,0000,,And that moment could change your life,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.33,0:18:02.72,main,HANAKO,0000,0000,0000,,even if you don't understand\Nanything right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.33,0:18:04.72,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.72,0:18:07.02,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,The last six months flew by, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.02,0:18:08.94,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,A lot has happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.94,0:18:11.41,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,The qualifier, the training camp,\Nall the track meets.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.41,0:18:14.17,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,And we met Hana.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.65,0:18:18.14,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,She's been a huge help,\Nlike when Haiji collapsed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.14,0:18:20.33,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah. I remember that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.33,0:18:22.10,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,And she always comes to our practices.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.10,0:18:23.58,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. She's a huge help.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.58,0:18:25.60,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,Without Hana, we wouldn't have made it this far.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.60,0:18:26.76,main,TWIN,0000,0000,0000,,And she's cute.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.60,0:18:32.54,main,SHINDO,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.54,0:18:34.75,main,SHINDO,0000,0000,0000,,Where did Haiji go?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.43,0:18:36.23,main,PRINCE,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.98,0:18:39.73,main,PRINCE,0000,0000,0000,,You're asking me?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.73,0:18:42.81,main,SHINDO,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to discuss the roadside\Nplacement of our members.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.81,0:18:46.93,main,SHINDO,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, and the university's\Nasking us to turn in our forms.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.93,0:18:48.52,main,SHINDO,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever. Sorry to have bothered you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.86,0:18:51.98,main,PRINCE,0000,0000,0000,,That was close.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.66,0:18:56.15,main,PRINCE,0000,0000,0000,,I almost asked if he wanted my help.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.64,0:19:03.91,main,MUSA,0000,0000,0000,,It's shocking to know we can't win.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.22,0:19:09.33,main,MUSA,0000,0000,0000,,But I was saved by Haiji's words.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.03,0:19:12.29,main,MUSA,0000,0000,0000,,All we can do right now \Nis run as hard as we can.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.29,0:19:13.79,main,MUSA,0000,0000,0000,,He's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.79,0:19:23.76,Congrats_19:13(Ep 17),SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Congratulations Kansei University Long Distance Track and Field Team
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.61,0:19:17.36,main,MUSA,0000,0000,0000,,My anxieties have been\Neliminated completely.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.77,0:19:21.53,main,MUSA,0000,0000,0000,,Is there still something bothering you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.53,0:19:23.76,main,KAKERU,0000,0000,0000,,No. I agree.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.76,0:19:26.62,main,KAKERU,0000,0000,0000,,But it's frustrating.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.68,0:19:32.02,main,KAKERU,0000,0000,0000,,Sakaki made Jota and Joji anxious,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.02,0:19:34.44,main,KAKERU,0000,0000,0000,,but the only thing I can do is run.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.87,0:19:37.40,main,MUSA,0000,0000,0000,,You're hard on yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.11,0:19:42.74,main,MUSA,0000,0000,0000,,Previewing the course made me realize
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.13,0:19:49.82,main,MUSA,0000,0000,0000,,that not you or Haiji, but{\i1} I{\i0} have\Nto finish some section of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.57,0:19:53.65,main,MUSA,0000,0000,0000,,I have to do what I can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.65,0:19:56.54,main,MUSA,0000,0000,0000,,There are things only you can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.54,0:20:01.34,main,MUSA,0000,0000,0000,,Believe in us and in yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.34,0:20:04.21,main,KAKERU,0000,0000,0000,,I will.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.78,0:20:04.87,Congrats_19:13(Ep 17),,0000,0000,0000,,Congratulations Kansei University Long Distance Track and Field Team
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.92,0:20:08.60,main,STUDENT,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, it's Kansei's Ekiden guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.60,0:20:11.48,main,STUDENT,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah. They were on the news.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.48,0:20:14.21,main,STUDENT,0000,0000,0000,,They've got an exchange student?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.21,0:20:17.44,main,STUDENT,0000,0000,0000,,I know. I wish they'd run an all-Japanese team.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.44,0:20:22.01,main,STUDENT,0000,0000,0000,,The school's probably paying\Nfor it to promote themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.01,0:20:23.27,main,MUSA,0000,0000,0000,,What are you going to tell them?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.53,0:20:26.05,main,MUSA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.05,0:20:28.95,main,KAKERU,0000,0000,0000,,But... it's ridiculous!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.95,0:20:31.40,main,KAKERU,0000,0000,0000,,We're all runners!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.40,0:20:32.50,main,KAZUMA,0000,0000,0000,,Kurahara.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.48,0:20:38.97,main,KAZUMA,0000,0000,0000,,It's been a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.61,0:20:43.55,main,KAKERU,0000,0000,0000,,Fujioka?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.05,0:20:49.81,University_hospital_20:47(Ep 17),SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,University Hospital
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.10,0:20:53.02,main,NURSE,0000,0000,0000,,Kiyose. Kiyose Haiji.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.98,0:20:59.06,main,HAIJI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
